%S A394949 1,1,4,16,70,316,1496,7262,36125,182892,939930,4889397,25697696,
%T A394949 136246850,727848980,3913926874,21168870664,115082573677,628505354627,
%U A394949 3446616041324,18970906373519,104772011112388,580410325298722,3224368725260893,17958697907545749,100262386745980236
%N A394949 Number of equivalence classes of well-formed bracketed words of total length 2n built from the symbol * (of length 2) and three unary bracket types (), [], and {}, with no empty bracket pair, modulo commutativity of concatenation.
%C A394949 a(0)=1 counts the empty word.
%C A394949 For n>=1, a(n)=b_{3,2}^m(2n) in the notation of Au and Bremner; see Section 4.1.
%C A394949 Here two bracketed words are equivalent if they differ only by permuting factors in any concatenation.
%C A394949 The three unary bracket types are distinguished and do not commute under nesting.
%C A394949 Equivalently, a(n) counts rooted unordered trees with n vertices in which each leaf represents *, each unary internal node is labeled 1, 2, or 3, and every non-unary internal node has at least 2 unordered children.
%H A394949 Yu Hin Au and Murray R. Bremner, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.25731">Enumerating Multi-Operator Monomials in Commutative and Noncommutative Settings</a>, arXiv:2604.25731 [math.CO], 2026. See pp. 4, 28 (Table 7).
%F A394949 G.f.: 1 + A(x) = exp(Sum_{k>=1} (x^k + 3*x^k*A(x^k))/k).
%F A394949 n*a(n) = c(n) + Sum_{k=1..n-1} c(k)*a(n-k) for n>1, with a(0)=a(1)=1, where c(n) = Sum_{m|n} m*b(m), b(1)=1, and b(n)=3*a(n-1) for n>=2.
%e A394949 a(3)=16 = 1 + 6 + 9: one class represented by ***, 6 classes represented by P_i(**) and P_i(*)* for i=1,2,3, and 9 classes represented by P_i(P_j(*)) for i,j in {1,2,3}.
%Y A394949 Cf. A000081, A394948, A394950, A007564.
%K A394949 nonn,easy,new
%O A394949 0,3
